Mr. Moshood Ayinde, a commercial driver, has commended the efforts of the Federal Government and the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) for the work on the Lagos-Ibadan expressway to alleviate the plight of travelers during the Yuletide season. Ayinde told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Ibadan on Thursday that the trip from Ibadan to Lagos on the eve of Christmas, was free and memorable without the usual gridlock at Mowe – Ibafo axis of the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway. Ayinde said that the slight traffic gridlock experienced from Ibafo to Magboro axis was due to the road diversion as a result of the ongoing construction by Julius Berger. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He expressed gratitude to the Federal Government for the ongoing construction work on the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway. According to him, when the road is completed, the gridlock being experienced will definitely become a thing of the past and reduce travel time. Soldiers kill Three Armed Robbers In Plateau 10 Injured As Driver Sleeps Off While Driving Passenger Bus   In Awka Also, Mr Awoyemi Kolade, a driver, called on the security agencies to increase patrols on the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway due to constant attacks by armed robbers at night especially during gridlock. Kolade said that armed robbers usually took advantage of the traffic gridlock around Ibafo and Magboro axis to attack motorists and sometimes destroyed their vehicles. A traveler, Mr Salah Aribi, also commended the administration of President Muhammadu Buhari for constantly releasing money for the ongoing construction on the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway and other road across the country. Aribi said the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway was now motorable and most of the potholes on the road has been repaired. Another traveler on the road, Mr. Ayodele Olopade, said that the heavy traffic experienced recently on the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway was terrible.“I don’t know how we can make that road better but it can be better. “The gridlock is usually around Berger but recently it is between the boundary of Ibadan and Ogun State that we now experience serious traffic gridlock.” “The journey of one hour now take like three hours, ” Olopade said.The Chairman, Ikorodu Unit II Park Manager in Iwo road Garage, Mr Kola Alawode, urged government to expedite action on the ongoing construction on the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway.” Alawode said that gridlock was usually experienced at had portions of the highway, but noted that some potholes on the route had been repaired. He, however, said that commercial drivers experienced low number of travelers ahead of this Christmas compared to 2019 and attributed this to compliance with the Federal Government’s directive on COVID-19 restrictions. Alawode said that most people don’t want to travel due to the fear of COVID-19. The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) Sector Commander in Oyo State, Mrs. Uche Chukwurah, said her men had been deployed on the roads to ensure free flow of traffic and to remove obstructions on roads. She urged the motorists to always obey traffic rules and regulations and shun night travelling. NAN reports that the transport fare from Ibadan to Lagos by bus now cost N2,000 instead of N1,500 while the price by car now cost N2,500 instead of N2,000. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION